<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871117-0120 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Carson Pirie Scott andamp; Co.</HL><DD> 11/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CRN GTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)FOOD andamp; BEVERAGE, HOUSEHOLD GOODS, SUPERMARKETS, TOBACCO (FAB)DIVIDENDS (DIV) </IN><TEXT>   Carson Pirie Scott andamp; Co. said its stockholders approved Greyhound Corp.'s previously announced offer to buy its airline catering and airport terminal food operations for $326 million.    The Chicago-based department store chain said that if all conditions of the acquisition are satisfied, its stockholders will receive a special $30-a-share payment. The record date for the distribution is Nov. 27, the company said.    Greyhound is a Phoenix, Ariz.-based company with interests in consumer products and food services. </TEXT></DOC>